            showToastMsg: Displays a toast message on the browser OR on through Desktop Notifications (DN)

            Arguments:
                @cfg {string} represents the actual message to display without any other configuration parameter.

                @cfg {object} represents the configuration of a toast notification with the following structure:
                        title.....: (string) the title/caption of the notification (plain text)
                        msg.......: Optional (string) the body of the message (HTML not supported on DN)
                        text......: Optional (string) the message content (plain text)
                        html......: Optional (string) the message content (html, not supported on DN)
                        ui........: (string) "info", "success", "danger", "warning", ... represents the UI to display (NOTE: on DN, they are replaced by ad-hoc icons)
                        allowDN...: Optional (boolean). You can override the toast message behavior to include or avoid desktop notifications explicitly. (default: true)                         
                        autoHide..: Optional (boolean) Whether the message should close automatically (default: true)
                        delay.....: Optional (boolean) The amount of time (ms) the notification remains displayed before closing (default: 2000) 
                        
                        PROPERTIES SUPPORTED ONLY ON IN-BROWSER TOAST NOTIFICATIONS                        
